ARIEL uses most of the built-in XML Schema datatypes. 
References to these datatypes are by means of the URI 
reference for the datatype, http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema. 
The following datatypes are recommended for use with ARIEL:

xsd:string	
xsd:normalizedString	
xsd:boolean
xsd:decimal	
xsd:float	
xsd:double
xsd:integer	
xsd:nonNegativeInteger	
xsd:positiveInteger
xsd:nonPositiveInteger	
xsd:negativeInteger
xsd:long	
xsd:int	
xsd:short	
xsd:byte
xsd:unsignedLong	
xsd:unsignedInt	
xsd:unsignedShort	
xsd:unsignedByte
xsd:hexBinary	
xsd:base64Binary
xsd:dateTime	
xsd:time	
xsd:date	
xsd:gYearMonth
xsd:gYear	
xsd:gMonthDay	
xsd:gDay	
xsd:gMonth
xsd:anyURI	
xsd:token	
xsd:language
xsd:NMTOKEN	
xsd:Name	
xsd:NCName


